# Help & FAQ

## Our Story

2Lines was born out of a real need. When my wife and I started trying to conceive, we found ourselves juggling half a dozen apps — one for cycle tracking, another for BBT charting, a separate one for pregnancy week-by-week updates, yet another to time contractions, and a notes app to keep track of doctor visits and questions. None of them talked to each other, and none of them captured the full picture.

We wanted one place — a single pane of glass — to capture every detail of the journey from the first hopeful cycle all the way through to holding our baby. Every temperature reading, every heartbeat recording, every ultrasound photo, every nervous question before a doctor's appointment. All of it, together, in one beautiful timeline.

So I built it. What started as a side project for our family became 2Lines — named for those two little lines on a pregnancy test that change everything. We hope it helps your family the way it helped ours.

## Getting Started

### What is 2Lines?

2Lines is a conception-to-birth journey planner that guides you from trying to conceive, through pregnancy, and into life with your new baby. It combines evidence-based fertility tracking, pregnancy monitoring, and keepsake creation in one app.

### What do the journey phases mean?

**Trying to Conceive (TTC)**: Track your cycles, log fertility signs (BBT, cervical mucus, LH tests), and receive smart predictions for your most fertile days.

**Pregnant**: Track your pregnancy week by week with size comparisons, daily symptom logging, doctor visit management, kick counting, and contraction timing.

**Delivered**: Celebrate your journey with memory exports, keepsake creation, and a complete timeline of your experience.

## Fertility Tracking (TTC)

### How does 2Lines predict my fertile window?

2Lines uses the Symptothermal Method (STM), which is the gold standard for fertility awareness. It cross-references multiple signs: your basal body temperature (BBT) for the post-ovulatory thermal shift, cervical mucus patterns using the Billings Ovulation Method, LH test strip results, and secondary signs like cervical position and ovulation pain.

When two or more signs agree, prediction confidence increases. The more data you log, the more accurate predictions become.

### How accurate are the predictions?

Accuracy depends on how consistently you log data. Calendar-only predictions (based on cycle history alone) have the lowest confidence. Adding daily BBT readings, cervical mucus observations, and LH test results significantly improves accuracy. The Symptothermal Method has been shown to have 99.6% perfect-use efficacy in published research (Frank-Herrmann et al., 2007).

2Lines always labels the prediction method and confidence level — it never presents uncertain estimates as definitive.

### When should I take my BBT?

Take your BBT first thing in the morning before getting out of bed, at approximately the same time each day. Use a basal body thermometer (accurate to 0.01°F). Log the reading immediately in your daily log.

### What do the cervical mucus types mean?

- **Dry**: No noticeable mucus — low fertility
- **Sticky**: Thick, crumbly texture — low fertility
- **Creamy**: Smooth, lotion-like — moderate fertility, approaching ovulation
- **Watery**: Clear, wet, slippery — high fertility
- **Egg White (EWCM)**: Stretchy, clear, resembles egg whites — peak fertility, ovulation is near or occurring

### What is the fertile window?

The fertile window is the approximately 6-day period each cycle when conception is possible — the 5 days before ovulation plus ovulation day. Sperm can survive up to 5 days in fertile-quality cervical mucus, and the egg survives 12-24 hours after ovulation.

### Can I import cycle data from other apps?

Yes. Enable Apple Health integration in Settings > Apple Health. 2Lines imports historical cycle data from Apple Health, which receives data from apps like Flo, Clue, Natural Cycles, and Apple's built-in Cycle Tracking. Your in-app entries always take priority over imported data.

## Pregnancy Tracking

### How are gestational weeks calculated?

Gestational age is calculated from your last menstrual period (LMP) or your estimated due date. If you transition from TTC to Pregnant phase, 2Lines uses your tracked cycle data for the most accurate estimate.

### What is kick counting?

Starting around week 28, it's recommended to count your baby's movements daily. The standard method is to count 10 movements within 2 hours. If you enable kick count reminders, 2Lines will prompt you each evening.

### When should I start timing contractions?

Begin timing contractions when you notice regular, painful tightening. The 5-1-1 rule suggests heading to the hospital when contractions are 5 minutes apart, lasting 1 minute each, for at least 1 hour. 2Lines tracks your contraction patterns and checks against this rule automatically.

## Exports & Keepsakes

### What can I export?

2Lines+ subscribers can export: Memory Book PDF, Video Slideshow (with heartbeat audio), Heartbeat Audio Compilation, Birth Plan PDF, Hospital Bag Checklist, BBT Chart, Contraction Log, Doctor Visits History, Medical Summary, and Data CSV.

All PDFs feature professional branded templates. Exports can be shared via email, AirDrop, printed, or saved to Files.

### How does the heartbeat compilation work?

Each time you record your baby's heartbeat at an appointment, 2Lines saves it as an individual clip you can play anytime. When you export the "Heartbeat Compilation," all clips are merged chronologically into a single continuous audio file with short gaps between clips. This compiled audio also serves as the soundtrack for the Video Slideshow.

